caption: Warning because I didn't know, but their website ordering doesn't work. So if you use google maps to order from, do not use their own website. Use one of the 3rd party apps to order, even if you're doing pick up, or call your order in...  Because I ordered my food online and it didn't work, when I got to the restaurant to pick up my order, it obviously wasn't ready because the lady didn't even get my order in the first place, BUT, she was super apologetic and kind about it.  She felt really bad and got my order in and done as quickly as possible with only one person cooking, and other people in the restaurant.  As for the food, it was really tasty.  We ordered the ceviche sampler, and the flavors were so good, the fish, talk, shrimp, was perfect. Order this if you love lime, cilantro and seafood.  We also order the seafood rice, Arroz con Mariscos, It was really good as well, the spanish rice with the seafood flavors, so much crab too. Awesome.  The seco de carne the meat was sooo good, just wish it was cut smaller, but flavor was awesome. I don't like beans, so I can't comment on that, but my SO said it was good.  And last was the Lomo saltado, this was really flavorful too, make sure you dip the meat in the sauce. So good. So full.  Overall the food was really good, the customer service was really good as well.  We will definitely be ordering here again, but over the phone next time. 😆👍
Mimi's was delicious! The manager was very friendly and chatting up all the guests, making everyone feel welcome, we would come back here any day of the week.
The food was delicious and the service was so pleasant 🙂👍

Mimi's tallarin saltado de carne (beef noodles) were ON POINT! My family of 9 had to quarantine after our travels and we were able to get a family style tray that fed my big family and even had some leftovers! It was a wonderful taste of peruvian flavors and definitely a much needed home style cooked meal. Mimi's will be our go-to and will be returning again!
DELICIOUS FOOD! She personally delivered the food to my family of 9 while in quarantine.

It was a delightful experience. Ray and I both ordered of the lunch specials menu...beef, and chicken. A small bowl of plantain chips and fried blue corn kernels. Delightful!  Fried corn kernels are so much better than popcorn! Who knew? The chicken were slices of breast meat, fried and covered in a flavorful sweet and spicy chili sauce. Served with salad, rice and French fries. I could skip the fries personally. Ray's beef plate was served with salad, rice and broad beans, cooked Peruvian style. I will definitely come back.

We were in Hawaii for our honeymoon earlier this year in March 2020 and we were both missing Peruvian food, so we decided to stop by. We ended up coming back a second time because the food was just so good! The owner and her mom were both there, they were both friendly and great conversationalists. We hope to come back someday!

I cannot give a fair rating because I love Peruvian food but I will say this place has great traditional Peruvian food. Owned and run by peruvians. Lots of nostalgia in this little place. Give it a try.
Great food and love the authenticity! They even have Chicha Morada! Slightly expensive (hence 4 stars), and would return if it were more affordable. Definitely a cozy space, but worth a visit.

Ok...Im not Latino so hopefully I don't butcher this....but Pescado a lo macho. This dish contains fresh, firm fish, shrimp snow crab, mussels, scallops and succulent Mahi Mahi in a broth i wanted to drink last. Of all the delicious Peruvian grinds you can get at this eatery....this is my new favorite! Probably until next week. Love and respect Mimi!

Mimi's Peruvian Cusine is a wonderful restaurant in Honolulu and one of only 2 Peruvian Restaurants on Ohau.  Mimi's is family owned and operated, frequented by local residents, and presents a menu that truly represents Peruvian cuisine.   Our son inlaw was born and raised in Peru and he rates the menu, food, and presentation as 5 plus stars.  The prices are reasonable, the portions are generous, and they have a great selection of fish and meats.  Do youself a favor, don't pass up the opportunity to enjoy a meal from Mimi's Peruvian Cuisine!

To be absolutely clear to this "owner", IT'S YOUR SERVICE THAT I HAVE A PROBLEM WITH. not just at the restaurant, but as it's CLEARLY reflected in the seeming lack of ability to take responsibility for your actions in HOW you're (only) addressing 1 and 2 star reviews. ---------- UPDATE: Based on the response from the "owner" I can see why I received such horrible service. You think I'm nitpicking because I'm in a hurry and I'm cheap?? Wow, your fake apology and insistence on making it my fault is perfectly in keeping with my experience at your restaurant. TAKE RESPONSIBILITY FOR YOUR BUSINESS. --------- We were the only other couple at the restaurant for lunch on a Saturday. As we put in our order, the person serving us told us some confusing story about the salad pictured. After about 10 or 15 minutes (!!), he comes out and tells us that he “checked” the slow cooked chicken that was a part of our other order and that it won’t be ready for another 30-40 minutes so I should choose something else. Absolutely no apology for the fact that he took that long to “check” on the chicken. No suggestion to help me make a decision and reduce the wait time. He just told me I need to pick something else and bounced. I decided not to pick anything else because I just didn't want to wait for the strangely slow moving service for the 4 of us that were in the restaurant. We ate the salad, got the bill and realized he was charging us for the more expensive salad plus an up charge for the chicken added to it. I tried to explain our side to clear up what our intentions were because at that point I wasn’t willing to pay 50% more for a salad that we had no intention of getting. Mimi's is located on Keeaumoku across from Walmart near Ross. The restaurant is small and can easily be missed. The restaurant is cozy when seating. The service is great. It is a small family operation so the care for great service is apparent. The food is delicious, the salchipapa comes with a variety of sauces. The Bistek and Seco De Carne are the best. The meat soft and the beans are the best anywhere. It has great flavors and an awesome variety of seafood and meats. The Tres Leches is the best dessert. We are definite repeat customers.

Authentic and delicious food! I was born in Venezuela and it reminds me of home. The ceviche (raw fish cooked in lime juice) was fresh and the best I’ve had on island. Their fresh juices maracuya (passion fruit) and chica morada (purple corn) are a most try. They also served delicious fried yucca fries with traditional dipping sauce.  Everything is fresh and authentic South American food. The staff was friendly and attentive. The location is convenient and the restaurant is decorated beautifully.  Lastly, pick up alfajores cookies on your way home. You won’t regret it ;) strongly recommend
100% the best ceviche on the island. This place is very small and very cute, and, most importantly to me, very authentic! I could not recommend Mimi's more highly!

This place is awesome! Peru has some really excellent chefs doing cool fusion dishes. Lima is full of hi end restaurants and they are not serving guinea pig or roast chicken and fries. Mimi's is in that vein. Excellent ceviche, beef, yucca and others I have to try. This is the first place in Hawaii that I have been that doesn't turn down the heat in the appropriate places. I have yet to be at a Thai restaurant in Hawaii that is even low heat in Thailand. But I degrees...food is excellent and.the place is small, the people are cool. Don't think of it as Peruvian food, think of it as excellent food made with a Peruvian influence. Get it while it's hot!

A great find in Oahu.  We started with a selection of appetizers, including the Jalea and Yucca Fritas, followed by the cebiche pescado.  The Yucca was fresh and fried to perfection.  The Jalea was delicious, with a house-made tartar sauce (it paired perfectly.)  The main event though was the cebiche.  The fish was fresh, and it was made in true Peruvian fashion with sweet potato (camote) on the side.  Perfectly seasoned and tender.  To drink, strong suggest the well-made Chicha Morada (a sweet drink made from boiling the stalks of purple corn found in Peru, and adding herbs and a touch of simple syrup.) Refreshing, especially in the summer.  To close, try the delicious house-made alfajores!
